    modified_response: "I have completed the Retro-Mod File Portal application, focusing on a visually authentic 90s nostalgic interface with modern reactivity. \n\n- **Classic Desktop Theme**: Designed an accurate retro aesthetic featuring a deep teal workspace, classic gray window structures (with custom CSS inset/outset border borders), and classic solid black drop shadows.\n- **Hierarchical Navigation**: Built an interactive sidebar tree view paired with an expansive main file grid, allowing you to easily traverse up and down nested folders. \n- **Interaction Model**: Implemented a classic click paradigm\342\200\224single-click focuses the item (turning it highlight blue), while double-clicking executes the action (opening the folder or launching the file viewer).\n- **File Previews**: Included a mock storage architecture populated with old-school system text files, images, and audio. Attempting to open a file will trigger an elegant modal window to preview the content seamlessly rather than kicking you to new tabs."
