  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Defining the System\'s Role**\n\nI\'m focusing on defining this file hosting system\'s role. The user\'s initial query, \"what do you call such a system,\" seems straightforward, but the subsequent input reveals its specifics: \"Oasis Resort Document Centre \342\200\224 File Hosting Inventory...\" This description clarifies its function as a file and folder inventory server. It\'s becoming clearer.\n\n\n**Integrating the Document Data**\n\nI\'m now integrating the user\'s Markdown-formatted inventory data. I\'m moving away from dummy data in `/src/data.ts` and updating it to reflect the Oasis Resort Document Centre structure. I\'ll need to update `/metadata.json` and layout files accordingly. I\'m focusing on statically hosting the provided data since I can\'t guarantee the URL\'s accessibility, although I could also allow dynamic fetching.\n\n\n**Refining the UI Data**\n\nI\'m now refining the UI data and addressing how to respond when the user asks, \"What do you call such a system?\" I realize I need to answer AND update the UI, including the data in `data.ts`. The provided Markdown inventory data, representing the \"Oasis Resort Document Centre,\" will be directly integrated. The system is designed to provide quick and clear navigation of nested PDF files, as shown in the example inventory.\n\n\n**Structuring the Document Data**\n\nI\'m now structuring the document data within `src/data.ts`. I\'m focusing on defining the types, specifically adding \"pdf\" as a \"document\" type. I\'m updating the existing structure to reflect the given data, creating the necessary folders and documents within the data. I\'ve started defining `rootFolder`, now including `Board-Minutes`, along with PDF files like \"January-13-2026-Board-minutes.pdf\".\n\n\n**Organizing Folder Data**\n\nI\'m now integrating more folder and file data. I\'ve added a \"Financial-Statements\" folder, and a \"Forms\" folder with some PDF documents. I\'m ensuring everything is correctly formatted, with sizes and update times included for each item in `src/data.ts`.\n\n\n**Adding More Folder Data**\n\nI\'ve integrated new folder and file data, focusing on insurance-related documents now. This includes adding the \"Insurance\" folder with PDFs like \"Oasis.Q1.2026.pdf\" and \"Oasis.Q2.NTR_.pdf\". I\'ve also added the file \".htaccess\" as an \"unknown\" file type, with its size and an explanation of its purpose. I\'m focusing on populating `src/data.ts` precisely.\n\n\n"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 31
      nanos: 45976022
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
