  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Designing the Interface**\n\nI\'ve been working on the aesthetic shift, and I\'m really pleased with how the tools automatically generated a modern, user-friendly interface. It\'s got the iPad/macOS feel, with rounded corners, large text, and a simple \"Back\" button, as well as clear breadcrumbs. The design is now in a pretty usable state.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I have completely rebuilt the interface to utilize a modern, highly legible \"Apple-like\" aesthetic optimized for a smooth user experience.\n\nHere is an overview of the new design updates:\n* **MacOS / iPadOS Visual Identity**: Removed the dark retro shell and replaced it with a bright, ultra-clean glass-pane container. The app runs over a classic abstract, colorful background.\n* **Boomer-Friendly Legibility**: Removed all monospace and tiny fonts. Implemented the standard *Inter* (San Francisco alternative) typeface at a larger base size, ensuring high contrast and readable file names.\n* **Intuitive Navigation**: Replaced the nested retro file paths with an impossible-to-miss, touch-friendly \"Back\" button and bold breadcrumb trails. \n* **Enhanced Touch Targets**: Scaled up all icons, grid items, and buttons drastically so they function seamlessly as large click/touch targets. Selected items are now highlighted with a bright, obvious blue border and background instead of subtle dotted lines."
    thinking_duration {
      nanos: 138469052
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
